Description: Fix CVE-2025-58057 - Ensure decompression decoders fire buffers immediately
 This patch fixes a denial of service vulnerability where decompression
 decoders (Brotli, Zstd, Zlib) would accumulate buffers before forwarding
 them through the pipeline, potentially causing OutOfMemoryError when
 processing specially crafted compressed data (decompression bombs).
 The fix ensures buffers are fired through the pipeline as soon as
 possible and other handlers that use these decompressors will not
 buffer all of the produced data before processing it.
Origin: upstream, https://github.com/netty/netty/commit/34894ac73b02efefeacd9c0972780b32dc3de04f
Bug: https://github.com/advisories/GHSA-3p8m-j85q-pgmj
Author: Norman Maurer <norman_maurer@apple.com>
Last-Update: 2025-09-03

